


---

✅ Program 3: Check the Status of the Repository

Filename: program3_check_status.py


---

Objective:

To check the current status of a Git repository, including:

Which branch you're on

Whether there are any staged, unstaged, or untracked files

Whether the working tree is clean



---

Python Simulation Code:

# Program 3: Check Status of Repository
# SCM Lab Program – Git Status Simulation

print("----- Program 3: Check Git Repository Status -----")

print("Step 1: Make sure you are inside your Git repository folder.")
print("Command: cd myproject")

print("\nStep 2: Check the repository status.")
print("Command: git status")

print("\nExpected Output:")
print("On branch main")
print("nothing to commit, working tree clean")


